Tomorrow I turn 25!!!! Wow........
Yesterday my mom and drove down the mountain to Casa Grande to visit some relatives and some ruins...The temperature in Prescott when we left at about 1:30pm was probably around 50 degrees, and when we got to Phoenix two hours later it was about 70. It was fantastic!!!! I played my Train and Counting Crows CDs for my mom and she seemed to enjoy them, so that was cool :) Well, I'm off to write some more....it really stinks that the notes I made are in Ohio...

So I was lying down, starting to write a story, and I realized that I have not yet made a single entry in my journal!!! How dare i??

I am currently visiting my mom and step-dad in Prescott, AZ and I'm in the middle of a two week stay. It's so very beautiful out here--Thumb Butte is outside my window...And I'm from a place where they don't bother to name the cornfields; they just block the wind...

Things have been completely different out here, I haven't had any soda or sweets since I left Columbus Airport on the 25th, and I'm not really craving any, so I'm impressed with myself in that regard...

This afternoon, before going to T'ai Chi with my mom, I signed up for the National Novel Writing Month...I decided that I need to commit to writing again and the best way to do that is to have a goal!

Well, I'm going to get going on that novel; I need 50,000 words by November 30th!
